 Language: <F P=105>Russian </F>
Article Type:CSO 

<F P=106> [Article by N.A. Lavrov; UDC 621.592.3] </F>
  [Abstract] The promising properties of 
LaNi[.sup]5[/]-H[.sub]x[/] hydrides which can be ground 
into 5-7 æm powder with a bulk density of 3,240 
kg/m[.sup]3[/] and a 0.55 W/m[.sup].[/]K effective thermal 
conductivity, e.g., for use in hydride compressors for 
space-based hydrogen refrigerators where heat is supplied by the 
sun and removed by radiators, prompted attempts to optimize the 
